 <H1>Components of a Disk </H1> 
 <P><UL></P>

<P><LI> The platters spin (say, 90rps).
</UL></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI> The arm assembly is moved in or out to position  a head on a desired track. Tracks under heads  make    a cylinder (imaginary!).
</UL></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI> Only one head reads/writes at any one time.
</UL></P>

<P><UL></P>

<P><LI> Block size is a multiple             of sector size (which is fixed).</UL></P>

